“I thought so. Not so much anymore… What- what are you doing?” https://t.co/xMJPPXoGpn
The dragon looks around before going to take a seat in the grass where they think a picnic would be well placed. While doing so they repeat the oddly familiar name in their head like a broken record.

He seems uncertain but nods slowly at the request, not seeing any harm in it. 
Their memories of this man are so incredibly shattered, but he was always kind. 

Besides, they were fairly hungry after their hike down the mountain.
“A picnic would be lovely.. Xiao.” https://t.co/0CC0oIjHau

Then they are looking around for anyone else before quietly questioning Xiao, 
“Moonstone..?”

Albedo is quick to turn around and take in the sight of their new company, mismatched gaze lingering on the basket and the flowers. They could not tell if this was an unusual thing for him to have.

Quietly they move their gaze to his face.
+ https://t.co/frMHzgPMCn

“..Rai.” 

His name is heavy and familiar on their tongue. They sound like they’re telling himself his name.

“Hello.” Is all they can manage in their uncertainty.
